Section 5.2. Implications for Residue Serialization
================================================================

- This design has implications for how residues are serialized.  To
- ensure consistent interpretation, both SCHC endpoints must process
- entries in the same order.  Therefore:
+ This design has implications for how residues are serialized.  To
+ ensure consistent interpretation, all Instances participating in a
+ Session must process entries in the same order.  Therefore:

  *  Fields from the standard "entry" list MUST be serialized before
     those defined in the new "entry-option-space" list

- *This constraint should be documented in
- [I-D.ietf-lpwan-architecture] to ensure interoperability
+ *  This constraint follows the Context consistency considerations of
+    [I-D.ietf-schc-architecture]: the order of the entries of a Rule
+    is part of the Context and is preserved by Context distribution
+    and synchronization

